.TH "aa_path_perm" 9 "aa_path_perm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
aa_path_perm \- do permissions check & audit for @path
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" aa_path_perm
.BI "(const char *op "  ","
.BI "struct aa_label *label "  ","
.BI "const struct path *path "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ","
.BI "u32 request "  ","
.BI "struct path_cond *cond "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "op" 12
operation being checked
.IP "label" 12
profile being enforced  (NOT NULL)
.IP "path" 12
path to check permissions of  (NOT NULL)
.IP "flags" 12
any additional path flags beyond what the profile specifies
.IP "request" 12
requested permissions
.IP "cond" 12
conditional info for this request  (NOT NULL)
.SH "RETURN"
0 else error if access denied or other error
